trans-unit.source: The <see cref="T:System.Security.Permissions.WebBrowserPermission" /> object controls the ability to create the WebBrowser control.
In the Windows Presentation Foundation (WPF), the Web browser control enables frames to navigate HTML.
trans-unit.target: Dans Windows Presentation Foundation (WPF), le contrôle de navigateur Web vous permet d’accéder aux cadres de naviguer le HTML.

trans-unit.source: This permission uses the values of the <xref:System.Security.Permissions.WebBrowserPermission> enumerations.
trans-unit.target: Cette autorisation utilise les valeurs de la <xref:System.Security.Permissions.WebBrowserPermission> énumérations.

trans-unit.target: Cette classe n’est généralement pas utilisée en XAML.

trans-unit.source: Initializes a new instance of the <see cref="T:System.Security.Permissions.WebBrowserPermission" /> class.
Initializes a new instance of the <see cref="T:System.Security.Permissions.WebBrowserPermission" /> class.
By default, the value of the <xref:System.Security.Permissions.WebBrowserPermission.Level%2A> property is set to <xref:System.Security.Permissions.WebBrowserPermissionLevel.Safe>.
trans-unit.target: Par défaut, la valeur de la <xref:System.Security.Permissions.WebBrowserPermission.Level%2A> est définie sur <xref:System.Security.Permissions.WebBrowserPermissionLevel.Safe>.

trans-unit.source: An enumerated value of <see cref="T:System.Security.Permissions.PermissionState" />.
Initializes a new instance of the <see cref="T:System.Security.Permissions.WebBrowserPermission" /> class by specifying a permission state.

If `state` is set to <xref:System.Security.Permissions.PermissionState.Unrestricted>, the value of the <xref:System.Security.Permissions.WebBrowserPermission.Level%2A> property is set to <xref:System.Security.Permissions.WebBrowserPermissionLevel.Unrestricted>.
trans-unit.target: Si `state` a la valeur <xref:System.Security.Permissions.PermissionState.Unrestricted>, la valeur de la <xref:System.Security.Permissions.WebBrowserPermission.Level%2A> est définie sur <xref:System.Security.Permissions.WebBrowserPermissionLevel.Unrestricted>.

trans-unit.source: If `state` is set to <xref:System.Security.Permissions.PermissionState.None>, the value of the <xref:System.Security.Permissions.WebBrowserPermission.Level%2A> property is set to <xref:System.Security.Permissions.WebBrowserPermissionLevel.None>.
trans-unit.target: Si `state` a la valeur <xref:System.Security.Permissions.PermissionState.None>, la valeur de la <xref:System.Security.Permissions.WebBrowserPermission.Level%2A> est définie sur <xref:System.Security.Permissions.WebBrowserPermissionLevel.None>.

trans-unit.source: A permission to intersect with the current permission.
It must be of the same type as the current permission.
Creates and returns a permission that is the intersection of the current permission and the specified permission.
The intersection of two permissions is a permission that describes the state that they both describe in common.
Only a demand that passes both original permissions will be valid for the intersected permission.

trans-unit.source: A permission that is to be tested for the subset relationship.
This permission must be of the same type as the current permission.
Determines whether the current permission is a subset of the specified permission.
<see langword="true" /> if the current permission is a subset of the specified permission; otherwise, <see langword="false" />.
The current permission is a subset of the specified permission if the current permission specifies a set of operations that is wholly contained by the specified permission.
trans-unit.target: L’autorisation actuelle est un sous-ensemble de l’autorisation spécifiée si l’autorisation actuelle spécifie un ensemble d’opérations qui est entièrement contenu par l’autorisation spécifiée.

trans-unit.source: For example, a permission that represents access to C:\example.txt is a subset of a permission that represents access to C:\\.
trans-unit.target: Par exemple, une autorisation qui représente l’accès à C:\example.txt est un sous-ensemble d’une autorisation qui représente l’accès à C:\\.

trans-unit.source: If this method returns `true`, the current permission represents no more access to the protected resource than does the specified permission.
trans-unit.target: Si cette méthode retourne `true`, l’autorisation en cours ne représente pas plus d’accès à la ressource protégée que l’autorisation spécifiée.

trans-unit.source: Returns a value indicating whether the current permission is unrestricted.

<see langword="true" /> if the <see cref="P:System.Security.Permissions.WebBrowserPermission.Level" /> property is set to <see cref="F:System.Security.Permissions.WebBrowserPermissionLevel.Unrestricted" />; otherwise, <see langword="false" />.
An unrestricted permission represents access to any and all resources protected by the permission.
trans-unit.target: Une autorisation sans restriction représente l’accès à toutes les ressources protégées par l’autorisation.
